author: Thomas Grove
title: Plane Carrying 71 People Crashes Near Moscow; Survivors Unlikely
text:
MOSCOW—A Russian airplane carrying 71 people crashed on the outskirts of Moscow on Sunday shortly after takeoff, Interfax reported.
The Russian-made An-148 had taken off from Moscow’s Domodedovo Airport and was flying over the outskirts of the capital when it caught fire and fell from the sky, Russia’s state TV reported eyewitnesses as saying. Russian authorities believed there were no survivors.
